scraper benchmarks game

scrapers solve two problems:

(1) getting the content
- HTTP requests with proper headers/cookies/sessions
- JS-rendered pages (headless browser vs plain HTTP, API calls)
- pagination and crawling link graphs
- authentication, rate limiting, IP bans, CAPTCHAs
- bot detection (fingerprinting, cloudflare, datadome, etc)
- dynamic selectors, shadow DOM, iframes, cookie banners

(2) parsing
- extracting structured data from HTML (CSS selectors, XPath)
- inconsistent/malformed markup and varying page layouts
- cleaning and normalizing text (encoding, dates/times, URLs)
- nested/recursive structures (comment threads, trees)

benchmarking challenges
- ground truth labelling
- reproducible snapshots/live website
- metrics (precision/recall per domain, ...).


